mainmenu "M5StickS3 validation app"

config APP_DISPLAY_DEMO
	bool "Diagnostics page colour-cycle + backlight blink"
	default y
	help
	  When enabled, the diagnostics page (PAGE_DIAG) cycles the LCD through
	  R/G/B/W fills and periodically blinks the backlight via the regulator
	  API, to exercise the display and the M5PM1 power-rail control on
	  hardware.

	  Disable it (for example -DCONFIG_APP_DISPLAY_DEMO=n) for a quiet
	  diagnostics page (static black fill); the other pages are unaffected.

config APP_BLE
	bool "BLE advertising + GATT telemetry"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, the app brings up the Bluetooth LE controller and starts
	  connectable + scannable advertising that carries the device name and a
	  manufacturer-specific telemetry payload (uptime, battery mV, accel mg).
	  It also exposes a custom 128-bit GATT service with a READ + NOTIFY
	  telemetry characteristic, and adds a BLE status page to the UI.

	  This pulls in the full Bluetooth host + the Espressif controller HAL,
	  so it requires the binary blob: run `west blobs fetch hal_espressif`
	  before building. It is off by default so the standard build stays
	  blob-free. Enable it via -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=overlay-ble.conf, which also
	  turns on CONFIG_BT and the peripheral role.

config APP_AUDIO
	bool "ES8311 audio (440 Hz beep)"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, the app brings up the on-board ES8311 codec on I2S0 and
	  adds an AUDIO page that plays a short 440 Hz beep when the page is
	  entered. The AW8737 speaker amplifier (M5PM1 GPIO3) is enabled only for
	  the duration of the beep.

	  This needs CONFIG_AUDIO / CONFIG_AUDIO_CODEC (ES8311) and CONFIG_I2S
	  (esp32-i2s + DMA). It is off by default so the standard build is
	  unchanged; enable it via -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=overlay-audio.conf, which
	  turns on the codec, I2S, and DMA Kconfigs.

config APP_IR
	bool "IR transmit + receive (NEC)"
	default n
	help
	  When enabled, the app brings up consumer-IR (NEC) on the StickS3 IR LED
	  (G46) and IR receiver (G42), and adds an IR page that transmits a test NEC
	  frame on entry and shows the last decoded address/command.

	  Zephyr 4.4 has no ESP32 RMT driver, so IR uses stock PWM peripherals: the
	  LEDC PWM generates the ~38 kHz carrier (TX) and MCPWM input capture reads
	  the receiver (RX); the NEC envelope and decoding live in app/src/nec.c. It
	  is off by default so the standard build is unchanged; enable it via
	  -DEXTRA_CONF_FILE=overlay-ir.conf, which turns on CONFIG_PWM and
	  CONFIG_PWM_CAPTURE. Uses no binary blobs.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
